‘Abortion is a catchment device for young women, and ultimately the fall out is that they become infected and become HIV positive. This terming of abortion as a contraceptive tool is a vehicle for the introduction of the theory of men, women, condoms… Believing that abortion is a contraceptive method, which is used liberally, is eroding our moral fiber.’

Dr Donald Grayston opened his presentation by talking about When Words Collide. He used this term to describe when our unconscious words collide with our conscious words.

‘The most important words in our life are the words we say to ourselves. You have to get the words right in your consciousness first, then you can learn to change the words which are used in society. Words . . . those instruments of change. Our roots and our source for life.’
